00:01:09.650 --> 00:01:12.320 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So first
of all, your comments

00:01:12.320 --> 00:01:14.850 align:middle line:84%
and your responses to all that
before we even get into it.

00:01:14.850 --> 00:01:17.330 align:middle line:10%
>>ABKE: Well, I've always
had this passionate bent

00:01:17.330 --> 00:01:21.290 align:middle line:10%
towards saving Christianity
from fundamentalism, saving it

00:01:21.290 --> 00:01:26.220 align:middle line:10%
from patriarchal structures that
have captured it, in my opinion.

00:01:26.220 --> 00:01:29.600 align:middle line:84%
Almost nothing represents
the true teachings of Jesus

00:01:29.600 --> 00:01:33.270 align:middle line:84%
or the Jesus movement that began
in the first century Palestine.

00:01:33.270 --> 00:01:37.190 align:middle line:10%
And so I began diving into
the scholarship and studies

00:01:37.190 --> 00:01:41.600 align:middle line:10%
of first-century Jewish
Christianity to unpack how do we

00:01:41.600 --> 00:01:44.270 align:middle line:10%
get as close to the
source of the living

00:01:44.270 --> 00:01:47.930 align:middle line:10%
historical Jesus, the great
master Yeshua, the Nazarene.

00:01:47.930 --> 00:01:50.300 align:middle line:84%
What is the closest source
to learn about this man?

00:01:50.300 --> 00:01:51.750 align:middle line:90%
And what did he really teach?

00:01:51.750 --> 00:01:55.280 align:middle line:84%
Well, it has to be his Jewish
followers in the first century

00:01:55.280 --> 00:01:57.950 align:middle line:84%
before it became a
gentile religion, all

00:01:57.950 --> 00:02:00.060 align:middle line:84%
of Jesus's followers,
and Jesus himself,

00:02:00.060 --> 00:02:03.360 align:middle line:84%
were devout Hebrew,
Aramaic speaking Jews,

00:02:03.360 --> 00:02:06.430 align:middle line:84%
not gentile pagan
Greeks that spoke Greek.

00:02:06.430 --> 00:02:09.000 align:middle line:90%
And so we have a cultural--

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:11.500 align:middle line:84%
scholars call it "the
parting of the ways."

00:02:11.500 --> 00:02:14.910 align:middle line:84%
Sometime around
100 AD, after Paul

00:02:14.910 --> 00:02:17.320 align:middle line:84%
had done his gentile
ministry career,

00:02:17.320 --> 00:02:20.520 align:middle line:84%
the gentile Christian world
began to burgeon and explode

00:02:20.520 --> 00:02:22.710 align:middle line:84%
while the temple
was destroyed in 70

00:02:22.710 --> 00:02:25.502 align:middle line:84%
AD the Jewish Christians are
scattered across the diaspora.

00:02:25.502 --> 00:02:27.960 align:middle line:84%
And now the Christian religion
has been completely divorced

00:02:27.960 --> 00:02:28.770 align:middle line:90%
from of its--

00:02:28.770 --> 00:02:29.790 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Completely co-opted.

00:02:29.790 --> 00:02:30.832 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Or origins, yeah.

00:02:30.832 --> 00:02:34.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And we're going to
get into your wonderful research

00:02:34.200 --> 00:02:36.720 align:middle line:84%
on the Book of
the Hebrews, which

00:02:36.720 --> 00:02:40.230 align:middle line:84%
is what you're talking about,
some really ancient texts that

00:02:40.230 --> 00:02:41.260 align:middle line:90%
survived.

00:02:41.260 --> 00:02:44.390 align:middle line:84%
So first, let's get into
your background a bit.

00:02:44.390 --> 00:02:48.640 align:middle line:84%
And as a son of a preacher,
and then becoming one yourself,

00:02:48.640 --> 00:02:50.400 align:middle line:84%
your days in church,
which were very

00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:52.530 align:middle line:84%
different than what
you experienced once

00:02:52.530 --> 00:02:53.920 align:middle line:90%
you became a preacher.

00:02:53.920 --> 00:02:54.220 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Oh yeah.

00:02:54.220 --> 00:02:56.053 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's talk
about your childhood

00:02:56.053 --> 00:02:58.340 align:middle line:84%
as a preacher's son and then
the choice to become one.

00:02:58.340 --> 00:02:59.260 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Yeah, yeah.

00:02:59.260 --> 00:03:02.500 align:middle line:84%
Well, my passion today
is to do everything

00:03:02.500 --> 00:03:05.030 align:middle line:84%
I can to either
reform Christianity,

00:03:05.030 --> 00:03:08.420 align:middle line:84%
back to the teachings of Jesus
that they have, in my opinion,

00:03:08.420 --> 00:03:11.140 align:middle line:84%
completely abandoned for
the teachings of Paul,

00:03:11.140 --> 00:03:14.530 align:middle line:84%
because I grew up as a, like you
said, third-generation pastor's

00:03:14.530 --> 00:03:16.700 align:middle line:90%
son in Evangelical Christianity.

00:03:16.700 --> 00:03:18.530 align:middle line:84%
And I was just a super
devout Christian.

00:03:18.530 --> 00:03:20.060 align:middle line:90%
I love Jesus with all my heart.

00:03:20.060 --> 00:03:22.220 align:middle line:84%
I was not like a fake
Christian in any way.

00:03:22.220 --> 00:03:23.740 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I thought
everybody else

00:03:23.740 --> 00:03:26.030 align:middle line:84%
was kind of a milquetoast
Christian compared to me.

00:03:26.030 --> 00:03:27.190 align:middle line:90%
I was all in.

00:03:27.190 --> 00:03:27.990 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:03:27.990 --> 00:03:29.980 align:middle line:84%
>>ABKE: And I went to
Oral Roberts University

00:03:29.980 --> 00:03:32.650 align:middle line:84%
to get my bachelor's degree,
a double bachelor's in music

00:03:32.650 --> 00:03:35.740 align:middle line:84%
and theology, to begin my
ministry career as a worship

00:03:35.740 --> 00:03:38.650 align:middle line:84%
pastor, because I grew up,
playing worship music in church

00:03:38.650 --> 00:03:39.890 align:middle line:90%
and leading worship.

00:03:39.890 --> 00:03:41.680 align:middle line:84%
And I wanted to
eventually follow

00:03:41.680 --> 00:03:43.390 align:middle line:84%
in my dad and
grandfather's footsteps

00:03:43.390 --> 00:03:44.990 align:middle line:90%
and be a senior pastor one day.

00:03:44.990 --> 00:03:47.200 align:middle line:84%
So I was going to start
as a worship minister

00:03:47.200 --> 00:03:48.440 align:middle line:90%
and go from there.

00:03:48.440 --> 00:03:52.450 align:middle line:84%
And my dad's church, our church
was very spirit-filled, not

00:03:52.450 --> 00:03:54.420 align:middle line:90%
fundamentalist, not legalistic.

00:03:54.420 --> 00:03:55.220 align:middle line:90%
We were doing--

00:03:55.220 --> 00:03:56.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You said, no hell.

00:03:56.090 --> 00:03:56.990 align:middle line:90%
There was no hell.

00:03:56.990 --> 00:03:58.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ABKE: Yeah, we never
taught about hell.

00:03:58.400 --> 00:04:00.830 align:middle line:84%
I think we secretly believed
it and all the same stuff,

00:04:00.830 --> 00:04:02.020 align:middle line:84%
but we never wanted
to talk about it.

00:04:02.020 --> 00:04:02.930 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It wasn't the focus.

00:04:02.930 --> 00:04:03.740 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Not at all.

00:04:03.740 --> 00:04:06.490 align:middle line:84%
And so I had the
luxury of avoiding

00:04:06.490 --> 00:04:08.530 align:middle line:84%
grappling with those
dogmatic beliefs

00:04:08.530 --> 00:04:12.580 align:middle line:84%
until I got my first
full-time pastoral job at 23.

00:04:12.580 --> 00:04:15.205 align:middle line:84%
And the story is, I was sitting
in the front row of the church,

00:04:15.205 --> 00:04:16.269 align:middle line:90%
my very first Sunday.

00:04:16.269 --> 00:04:16.899 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Wait a moment.

00:04:16.899 --> 00:04:17.410 align:middle line:90%
Before you even got that.

00:04:17.410 --> 00:04:17.860 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Yeah.

00:04:17.860 --> 00:04:19.195 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's talk about
the interview process.

00:04:19.195 --> 00:04:20.029 align:middle line:90%
Here, they see--

00:04:20.029 --> 00:04:20.987 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Oh, yeah, yeah.

00:04:20.987 --> 00:04:22.750 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --this
gorgeous young person

00:04:22.750 --> 00:04:24.560 align:middle line:90%
that knows the Bible coming in.

00:04:24.560 --> 00:04:25.602 align:middle line:90%
Their churches are dying.

00:04:25.602 --> 00:04:26.435 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: All of them.

00:04:26.435 --> 00:04:28.540 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: All over the
world, everywhere I go.

00:04:28.540 --> 00:04:30.650 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter what
the denomination is.

00:04:30.650 --> 00:04:31.970 align:middle line:90%
Few old people left.

00:04:31.970 --> 00:04:34.760 align:middle line:84%
And this was no different
in your community, right?

00:04:34.760 --> 00:04:36.080 align:middle line:90%
So let's talk about that.

00:04:36.080 --> 00:04:38.240 align:middle line:84%
And they wanted--
like, yes, we want him.

00:04:38.240 --> 00:04:41.890 align:middle line:84%
>>ABKE: Yeah, well, I knew
church attendance was shrinking

00:04:41.890 --> 00:04:43.537 align:middle line:90%
and dwindling, even back then.

00:04:43.537 --> 00:04:45.620 align:middle line:84%
Everybody was aware of it
and would talk about it.

00:04:45.620 --> 00:04:47.230 align:middle line:84%
But it's because the
end times are coming

00:04:47.230 --> 00:04:49.188 align:middle line:84%
and everything's going
to hell in a handbasket.

00:04:49.188 --> 00:04:50.510 align:middle line:90%
That's why church is shrinking.

00:04:50.510 --> 00:04:53.350 align:middle line:84%
And there's a study
that churchtrack.com

00:04:53.350 --> 00:04:57.640 align:middle line:84%
did that showed that 1.2
million Americans per year

00:04:57.640 --> 00:04:58.910 align:middle line:90%
stop going to church.

00:04:58.910 --> 00:05:02.540 align:middle line:84%
I think it's something like
10% decline every 12 years.

00:05:02.540 --> 00:05:03.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mm-hmm.

00:05:03.340 --> 00:05:04.180 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: That's huge.

00:05:04.180 --> 00:05:06.920 align:middle line:84%
And so every church I
interviewed at, there was five,

00:05:06.920 --> 00:05:10.415 align:middle line:84%
all of them had the same exact
reason for wanting to hire me.

00:05:10.415 --> 00:05:12.290 align:middle line:84%
They said, look, our
church is getting older.

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:13.670 align:middle line:90%
There's no young people here.

00:05:13.670 --> 00:05:15.327 align:middle line:84%
We need to get some
young blood in so

00:05:15.327 --> 00:05:16.910 align:middle line:84%
that we can attract
more young people,

00:05:16.910 --> 00:05:18.535 align:middle line:84%
or our congregation
is going to die out

00:05:18.535 --> 00:05:19.760 align:middle line:90%
in 10 years or something.

00:05:19.760 --> 00:05:22.660 align:middle line:84%
And I started to realize,
wow, every single church

00:05:22.660 --> 00:05:24.500 align:middle line:84%
I'm interviewing at
has this problem.

00:05:24.500 --> 00:05:28.670 align:middle line:84%
And so when I finally took my
first time position at a church,

00:05:28.670 --> 00:05:31.040 align:middle line:84%
I started to realize why
nobody goes to church anymore,

00:05:31.040 --> 00:05:32.510 align:middle line:90%
nobody my age, at least.

00:05:32.510 --> 00:05:34.720 align:middle line:84%
So I was sitting
in the front row.

00:05:34.720 --> 00:05:37.580 align:middle line:84%
And this woman goes on stage
to give an offering testimony.

00:05:37.580 --> 00:05:40.580 align:middle line:84%
And there's this man standing
behind her, kind of stoically.

00:05:40.580 --> 00:05:43.610 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, please be a
security guard or something.

00:05:43.610 --> 00:05:44.410 align:middle line:90%
Please--

00:05:44.410 --> 00:05:46.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Why would she
need one this Sunday?

00:05:46.430 --> 00:05:48.230 align:middle line:84%
>>ABKE: Yeah, I've never
seen this before in church.

00:05:48.230 --> 00:05:50.147 align:middle line:84%
I've never seen a man
standing behind a woman.

00:05:50.147 --> 00:05:52.187 align:middle line:84%
And in my mind, I know
the Bible pretty well.

00:05:52.187 --> 00:05:54.020 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking about all
the verses from Paul,

00:05:54.020 --> 00:05:55.470 align:middle line:90%
and I think First Timothy.

00:05:55.470 --> 00:05:57.480 align:middle line:84%
So I'm sitting there
in the front row,

00:05:57.480 --> 00:05:59.310 align:middle line:84%
hoping I'm not seeing
what I'm seeing.

00:05:59.310 --> 00:06:02.022 align:middle line:84%
And sure enough, she
goes down from the stage,

00:06:02.022 --> 00:06:03.980 align:middle line:84%
and they sit next to each
other and hold hands.

00:06:03.980 --> 00:06:06.860 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking
over going, dang it,

00:06:06.860 --> 00:06:10.200 align:middle line:84%
I'm at a super
fundamentalist church

00:06:10.200 --> 00:06:11.970 align:middle line:84%
that I didn't realize
was this legalistic.

00:06:11.970 --> 00:06:13.970 align:middle line:84%
And I don't want to be
at a church that believes

00:06:13.970 --> 00:06:15.330 align:middle line:90%
women are inferior to men.

00:06:15.330 --> 00:06:16.490 align:middle line:90%
Are you kidding me?

00:06:16.490 --> 00:06:18.200 align:middle line:84%
And I had just gotten
married as well.

00:06:18.200 --> 00:06:19.050 align:middle line:90%
I was 23.

00:06:19.050 --> 00:06:20.570 align:middle line:90%
My wife, at the time, was 20.

00:06:20.570 --> 00:06:23.300 align:middle line:84%
And we got home, and
she's upset and angry.

00:06:23.300 --> 00:06:24.600 align:middle line:90%
Can you believe they did that?

00:06:24.600 --> 00:06:25.920 align:middle line:84%
Can you believe they
believed that stuff here?

00:06:25.920 --> 00:06:27.080 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, I
know, sweetheart,

00:06:27.080 --> 00:06:28.372 align:middle line:90%
we're going to figure this out.

00:06:28.372 --> 00:06:30.172 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You were
really blowing back

00:06:30.172 --> 00:06:31.130 align:middle line:90%
against fundamentalism.

00:06:31.130 --> 00:06:31.970 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Oh, yeah.

00:06:31.970 --> 00:06:33.473 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Not
against Christianity.

00:06:33.473 --> 00:06:34.640 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Well, yeah, I mean--

00:06:34.640 --> 00:06:36.180 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But still,
it took you down.

00:06:36.180 --> 00:06:36.980 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: It did.

00:06:36.980 --> 00:06:38.727 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to save Christianity.

00:06:38.727 --> 00:06:40.310 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to save my
religion because I

00:06:40.310 --> 00:06:41.310 align:middle line:90%
was a devout Christian.

00:06:41.310 --> 00:06:44.660 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't even have known who
Aaron Abke is without being

00:06:44.660 --> 00:06:45.870 align:middle line:90%
a Christian back then.

00:06:45.870 --> 00:06:47.480 align:middle line:84%
And the idea of
leaving Christianity

00:06:47.480 --> 00:06:49.830 align:middle line:90%
was horrifyingly scary to me.

00:06:49.830 --> 00:06:51.800 align:middle line:84%
Every single person I
know, family and friends,

00:06:51.800 --> 00:06:53.340 align:middle line:90%
are all devout Christians.

00:06:53.340 --> 00:06:55.710 align:middle line:84%
What am I going to do
if I leave Christianity,

00:06:55.710 --> 00:06:56.940 align:middle line:90%
start my life over?

00:06:56.940 --> 00:06:59.450 align:middle line:84%
And that took me many years
to grapple with that fear of,

00:06:59.450 --> 00:07:01.500 align:middle line:84%
like, yes, I am going
to blow up my life,

00:07:01.500 --> 00:07:04.858 align:middle line:84%
everyone's going to heresy hunt
me, probably even my own family.

00:07:04.858 --> 00:07:06.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You'd lose everybody.

00:07:06.150 --> 00:07:06.450 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Yes.

00:07:06.450 --> 00:07:08.220 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: All social
contexts for your life.

00:07:08.220 --> 00:07:09.210 align:middle line:84%
>>ABKE: And that's
what happened.

00:07:09.210 --> 00:07:10.793 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So now you
leave the church.

00:07:10.793 --> 00:07:12.925 align:middle line:84%
And now you go pure
materials, right?

00:07:12.925 --> 00:07:14.007 align:middle line:90%
You decide to go into--

00:07:14.007 --> 00:07:16.590 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what you're doing
with your beliefs at that time.

00:07:16.590 --> 00:07:16.790 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Neither did I.

00:07:16.790 --> 00:07:19.457 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But you decide to go a
completely different direction.

00:07:19.457 --> 00:07:22.260 align:middle line:84%
You decide to really get into
working out, feeling your body.

00:07:22.260 --> 00:07:23.940 align:middle line:84%
And because you
look like you do,

00:07:23.940 --> 00:07:26.940 align:middle line:84%
you actually became a model
for the fitness industry.

00:07:26.940 --> 00:07:27.740 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Yeah.

00:07:27.740 --> 00:07:30.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Talk about that a
little bit and what that led to.

00:07:30.240 --> 00:07:33.180 align:middle line:84%
>>ABKE: Yeah, it led to
where I am today, for sure.

00:07:33.180 --> 00:07:35.720 align:middle line:84%
All the spiritual awakening
that I went through

00:07:35.720 --> 00:07:39.200 align:middle line:84%
after leaving Christianity
was just monumental

00:07:39.200 --> 00:07:41.845 align:middle line:90%
for me becoming who I am today.

00:07:41.845 --> 00:07:43.970 align:middle line:84%
And it started with leaving
Christianity and having

00:07:43.970 --> 00:07:46.940 align:middle line:84%
this identity crisis,
where I have no idea who

00:07:46.940 --> 00:07:48.750 align:middle line:90%
I am without Christianity.

00:07:48.750 --> 00:07:50.580 align:middle line:84%
And the only other
thing I had still

00:07:50.580 --> 00:07:53.325 align:middle line:84%
part of my ego at that point
was working out and exercise.

