00:12:58.005 --> 00:12:59.630 align:middle line:84%
that reading the Old
Testament, there's

00:12:59.630 --> 00:13:03.470 align:middle line:84%
clearly two different atonement
doctrines being taught.

00:13:03.470 --> 00:13:06.380 align:middle line:84%
In some passages, like
Leviticus, and more

00:13:06.380 --> 00:13:09.650 align:middle line:84%
in the Pentateuch, it's like,
hey, you got to kill an animal,

00:13:09.650 --> 00:13:11.680 align:middle line:84%
offer an animal on an
altar, spew its blood.

00:13:11.680 --> 00:13:12.930 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Seems rather random.

00:13:12.930 --> 00:13:16.440 align:middle line:84%
>>ABKE: Yeah, God wants
bloodshed to forgive you.

00:13:16.440 --> 00:13:18.020 align:middle line:84%
And, I mean, this
is a pagan practice

00:13:18.020 --> 00:13:21.320 align:middle line:84%
that historians and scholars
are clear about the origins of.

00:13:21.320 --> 00:13:24.320 align:middle line:84%
In ancient, ancient times,
primitive people began--

00:13:24.320 --> 00:13:27.360 align:middle line:84%
as they began believing in the
pantheon of gods and deities,

00:13:27.360 --> 00:13:30.830 align:middle line:84%
they wanted to derive ways
of bringing one of these gods

00:13:30.830 --> 00:13:32.780 align:middle line:84%
down to their tribe
and culture, and making

00:13:32.780 --> 00:13:35.030 align:middle line:84%
that god be their
master and give them

00:13:35.030 --> 00:13:38.360 align:middle line:84%
favor and fertility and
agriculture and war and all

00:13:38.360 --> 00:13:39.180 align:middle line:90%
these things.

00:13:39.180 --> 00:13:42.320 align:middle line:84%
And so they tried
to make these gods

00:13:42.320 --> 00:13:45.560 align:middle line:84%
a pet or something, where they'd
build a temple for the god

00:13:45.560 --> 00:13:48.902 align:middle line:84%
to live inside of,
offer the god sacrifices

00:13:48.902 --> 00:13:51.110 align:middle line:84%
on an altar to feed the
gods, so it would be pleased.

00:13:51.110 --> 00:13:53.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because these were
very valuable things to them.

00:13:53.430 --> 00:13:53.730 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Yes.

00:13:53.730 --> 00:13:56.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: An animal sacrifice
meant giving up something.

00:13:56.460 --> 00:13:58.940 align:middle line:84%
It was truly-- it was
the people's sacrifice,

00:13:58.940 --> 00:14:00.450 align:middle line:90%
to say nothing of the animal.

00:14:00.450 --> 00:14:01.250 align:middle line:90%
>>ABKE: Exactly.

00:14:01.250 --> 00:14:01.800 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:14:01.800 --> 00:14:03.710 align:middle line:84%
>>ABKE: And Jesus says
in the New Testament,

00:14:03.710 --> 00:14:05.640 align:middle line:90%
he quotes Hosea 6:6 twice.

00:14:05.640 --> 00:14:08.100 align:middle line:84%
In one of them, he says, go
and learn what this means.

00:14:08.100 --> 00:14:10.800 align:middle line:90%
I desire mercy, not sacrifice.

00:14:10.800 --> 00:14:12.335 align:middle line:84%
And if you knew
what this means, you

00:14:12.335 --> 00:14:15.310 align:middle line:84%
would not have condemned the
innocent, meaning the animals,

00:14:15.310 --> 00:14:16.110 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:14:16.110 --> 00:14:16.860 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:14:16.860 --> 00:14:18.890 align:middle line:84%
>>ABKE: Who else could be
innocent in an animal sacrifice

00:14:18.890 --> 00:14:20.035 align:middle line:90%
other than the animal?

00:14:20.035 --> 00:14:22.773 align:middle line:84%
It's not the sinner
offering the sacrifice.

00:14:22.773 --> 00:14:24.690 align:middle line:84%
And it's not the priest
that kills the animal.

00:14:24.690 --> 00:14:28.850 align:middle line:84%
So Jesus loved animals and
saw this practice of sacrifice

00:14:28.850 --> 00:14:30.660 align:middle line:90%
as abominable and detestable.

00:14:30.660 --> 00:14:33.240 align:middle line:84%
And Eusebius goes into great
length about this as well.

00:14:33.240 --> 00:14:36.180 align:middle line:84%
So Jesus emerged from this
sect we're talking about.

00:14:36.180 --> 00:14:39.110 align:middle line:84%
And so this sect
of Judaism began

00:14:39.110 --> 00:14:43.000 align:middle line:84%
prophesying against sacrifices,
especially through prophets

00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:46.210 align:middle line:84%
like Isaiah and Jeremiah,
who I consider to be

00:14:46.210 --> 00:14:48.610 align:middle line:90%
like proto-Essene prophets.

00:14:48.610 --> 00:14:51.350 align:middle line:84%
They were raging against
the sacrificial system.

00:14:51.350 --> 00:14:54.680 align:middle line:84%
And in Jeremiah 8
verse 8, he says,

00:14:54.680 --> 00:14:57.670 align:middle line:84%
"How can you say we are
wise, for the law of the Lord

00:14:57.670 --> 00:14:58.550 align:middle line:90%
is with us.

00:14:58.550 --> 00:15:01.960 align:middle line:84%
When, behold, the lying pen
of the scribes has turned it

00:15:01.960 --> 00:15:03.490 align:middle line:90%
into a lie."

00:15:03.490 --> 00:15:06.740 align:middle line:84%
And so he goes on in
chapter 7, as well,

00:15:06.740 --> 00:15:08.770 align:middle line:84%
saying, "God never
commanded us animal

00:15:08.770 --> 00:15:11.360 align:middle line:84%
sacrifices when we came
out of Egypt with Moses.

00:15:11.360 --> 00:15:15.110 align:middle line:84%
But here is what I commanded
you, O Israel, hear my voice,

00:15:15.110 --> 00:15:18.080 align:middle line:84%
obey my voice, and be my
people, and I will be your God."

00:15:18.080 --> 00:15:20.770 align:middle line:84%
So again, it's the 1
Samuel 15 of obedience

00:15:20.770 --> 00:15:22.370 align:middle line:90%
is better than sacrifice.

00:15:22.370 --> 00:15:24.310 align:middle line:84%
And I'd be reading the
Bible as a little boy

00:15:24.310 --> 00:15:26.800 align:middle line:84%
and be reading all these
passages of the prophets, just

00:15:26.800 --> 00:15:28.820 align:middle line:90%
railing against sacrifices.

00:15:28.820 --> 00:15:31.555 align:middle line:84%
I turn my nose away from
your abominable sacrifices,

00:15:31.555 --> 00:15:34.180 align:middle line:84%
I want nothing to do with them,
but give me righteousness, give

00:15:34.180 --> 00:15:37.313 align:middle line:84%
me humility, give me a pure
heart, is what God says.

00:15:37.313 --> 00:15:39.730 align:middle line:84%
And yet, then in Leviticus,
it's like, hey, kill an animal

00:15:39.730 --> 00:15:41.300 align:middle line:90%
if you want to be forgiven.

00:15:41.300 --> 00:15:44.290 align:middle line:84%
But in elsewhere, God says,
I forgive anyone who repents.

00:15:44.290 --> 00:15:47.170 align:middle line:84%
As long as you repent with a
truly humble and broken heart,

00:15:47.170 --> 00:15:49.420 align:middle line:84%
you turn your heart to me,
I forgive you of your sins.

00:15:49.420 --> 00:15:51.460 align:middle line:84%
So then why do we have
to butcher animals is

00:15:51.460 --> 00:15:52.760 align:middle line:90%
what the prophets were saying.

00:15:52.760 --> 00:15:55.250 align:middle line:84%
Obedience is better
than sacrifice.

00:15:55.250 --> 00:15:57.940 align:middle line:84%
So at a certain point, this
temple sacrifice system

00:15:57.940 --> 00:15:59.750 align:middle line:90%
had become such a behemoth.

